.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter that executes commands read from standard input.

.SH OVERVIEW
The shell reads commands from the terminal, validaties them and executes the commands.

.SH INVOCATION
Simple shell can be invoked by typing ./hsh in the terminal.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu] 2
Displays a prompt and waits for user input
.IP \[bu] 2
Executes simple command lines
.IP \[bu] 2
Handles EOF condition (Ctrl+D)
.IP \[bu] 2
Handles command lines with arguments
.IP \[bu] 2
Handles command exit

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B Interactive Mode:
.PP
$ ./hsh
.PP
#cisfun$ /bin/ls
.PP
file1 file2 file3
.PP
#cisfun$ exit
.PP
.B Non-Interactive Mode:
.PP
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.PP
file1 file2 file3

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns:
.IP \[bu] 2
0 for normal execution
.IP \[bu] 2
127 when command is not found
.IP \[bu] 2
1 for other errors

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell operates in the current environment of the user.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

